Hindi Livinus, Yola Adamawa State Governor, Ahmadu Fintiri, on Monday, presented a budget of N140.bn 2021 appropriation bill tagged “budget of stabilisation,” to the state assembly. The budget is made up of a recurrent expenditure of N67.2bn billion representing 48 per cent of the total Budget and N72.8bn for Capital development projects representing 52 per cent. Governor Ahmadu Fintiri on Monday presented a 2021 appropriation bill of N140, 034,409.00 to state lawmakers tagged as the budget of stabilization. Fintiri noted that although lawmakers approved the total sum of N183. 3bn for the 2020 fiscal year, N85.935bn out of this sum representing 47 per cent was earmarked for recurrent services and the balance of N97.424bn representing 53 per cent was for capital projects. The budget was subsequently revised downward to N140.072bn. He said the global economic challenges brought about by the Covid-19 Pandemic, made things difficult. Copyright PUNCH.
